Good morning Ramsin, thank you for sending over the additional documentation. This does help rectify the situation. Looks like they put the contract under the husband's name first, realized they made a mistake, voided the first contract and then put it in the wife's name. Either way, we have a solid contract and that's all we need. That being said, unfortunately the right side rear air spring is not a covered component under Margarita's contract. Fortunately, the replacement of the injector seals is. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, the customer's contract covers them for a maximum of $130/h for labour. If you choose to charge the quoted rate of $150/h, the customer will be responsible for the difference. Parts-$240.30
Labour-$585.00 (4.5 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00 + tax 
Tax-$94.29
Authorization-GQY29EMP13

Total = $819.59

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards, 

Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
